(NULL, 'The Konark Sun Temple, also known as the "Black Pagoda", was built during which dynasty?', 'Ganga Dynasty', 'Suryavanshi Dynasty', 'Chola Dynasty', 'Pala Dynasty', 'A', 1, 'Temples & Architecture', 'medium', '["Konark", "Temples", "History", "Architecture"]'::jsonb, 'The Konark Sun Temple was built in the 13th century CE by King Narasimhadeva I of the Eastern Ganga Dynasty.'),
(NULL, 'Which temple in Odisha is known as the "White Pagoda"?', 'Konark Sun Temple', 'Jagannath Temple, Puri', 'Lingaraj Temple, Bhubaneswar', 'Mukteswar Temple', 'B', 1, 'Temples & Architecture', 'easy', '["Jagannath", "Puri", "Temples"]'::jsonb, 'The Jagannath Temple in Puri is called the "White Pagoda" while Konark is called the "Black Pagoda".'),
(NULL, 'The Lingaraj Temple in Bhubaneswar is dedicated to which deity?', 'Lord Vishnu', 'Lord Shiva', 'Lord Krishna', 'Goddess Durga', 'B', 1, 'Temples & Architecture', 'medium', '["Lingaraj", "Bhubaneswar", "Temples", "Shiva"]'::jsonb, 'Lingaraj Temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is one of the oldest temples in Bhubaneswar, dating back to the 11th century.'),
(NULL, 'How many wheels are carved on the chariot of the Konark Sun Temple?', '12 wheels', '18 wheels', '24 wheels', '30 wheels', 'C', 1, 'Temples & Architecture', 'hard', '["Konark", "Architecture", "Sun Temple"]'::jsonb, 'The Konark Sun Temple is designed as a massive chariot with 24 elaborately carved stone wheels, representing the 24 hours of a day.'),

